        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 27 at 7:36PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 735 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Riverchase, or over Hoover, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hoover, Pelham, Helena, Indian Springs Village, Inverness,
Riverchase, Oak Mountain Amphitheater, Meadowbrook, Oak Mountain
State Park, and Hoover Veterans Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
